      <odd id="aspace_4dd607915050ca0ad66f849d0b47f656">
         <head>General note</head>
         <p>Forms part of Yale Record Group 4-A (YRG 4-A), Records of the Yale secretary's office.</p>  
      </odd>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_56420a971fe897a1b2c9a196bb6d1937">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>
         <p>Original audiovisual materials, as well as preservation and duplicating masters, may not be played. Researchers must consult use copies, or if none exist must pay for a use copy, which is retained by the repository. Researchers wishing to obtain an additional copy for their personal use should consult Copying Services information on the Manuscripts and Archives web site.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_578970b7d7a9fb3ff095911193da36f6">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Silliman Lecture Series, Yale University, Records (RU 360). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <arrangement id="aspace_3657abcf83ba527be0b7b41a6e2ce6d0">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The records are arranged by accession.</p>  
      </arrangement>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_120e84224d88577cd4dd2ff5b701be9b">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The records consist of audiotapes and videotapes documenting Eugene Shoemaker's 1996 lecture "Near Earth Asteroids and Comets" and James Anderson's 2002 lecture, and photographs and videorecordings documenting the Tercentenary Silliman Memorial Symposium, "A Remembrance of Times Past: The Development of Earth and Its Life."</p>  
      </scopecontent>
